ng questions of space, place, and mobility, Allison Glazebrook shows how sex laborers represented a diverse set of anxieties concerning social legitimacy and how the public discourse about them is in fact a discourse on Athenian society, values, and institutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aProstitutionxSocial aspectszGreecezAthensxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aProstitutionzGreecezAthensxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSpeeches, addresses, etc., GreekzGreecezAthens. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  asex work, Ancient Athens, Athenian courts, oratory, sexual labor, gender theory, ancient Greece, classical Athens, prostitution.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074527640uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32440040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477324417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477324417/original  a978-3-11-074527-6  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021